.TH CONFY 1 "2026-07-12" "3.0.0" "confy manual"
.SH NAME
confy \- a TUI config file manager for linux/unix systems
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B confy
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B confy
is a terminal-based config file manager. track, organize, and edit your config files from a single interface. supports groups, sorting, fuzzy search, rollback, custom colors and themes, a live preview pane, elevated editing via polkit, and browsing a remote host's tracked configs over sshfs.
.SH NAVIGATION
.TP
.B j / DOWN
move down
.TP
.B k / UP
move up
.TP
.B ENTER
open selected file in $EDITOR, or toggle group collapse
.TP
.B SPACE
toggle group collapse
.TP
.B p
toggle live preview pane
.TP
.B /
enter search mode (fuzzy search by filename or group)
.TP
.B :
enter command mode
.TP
.B q
quit
.SH COMMANDS
commands are entered by pressing
.B :
followed by the command name and ENTER.
.TP
.B :q
quit confy
.TP
.B :ac [group]
add a config file. opens the built-in file picker. optionally specify a group name.
.TP
.B :rm
remove the selected config file from tracking (does not delete the file)
.TP
.B :ag <name>
add a new group
.TP
.B :rg <name>
remove a group (files are moved to ungrouped)
.TP
.B :mg <name>
move selected file to a group
.TP
.B :l
reopen the last opened file
.TP
.B :rb
rollback the selected file to its last backup (saved automatically before each edit)
.TP
.B :su
open the selected file with root via
.BR pkexec (1)
\&. works on local files and on files viewed through a mounted
.B :device
alike. requires polkit; requires
.I user_allow_other
in
.I /etc/fuse.conf
to work through a mounted device.
.TP
.B :device <host>
.TQ
.B :ssh <host>
mount a remote host's root filesystem over sshfs and switch to browsing its tracked configs.
.I host
may be an alias from
.I ~/.ssh/config
or a literal
.IR user@host .
requires
.BR sshfs (1)
\&. refuses to connect if the remote is running a pre-3.0.0 confy without
.IR config.json .
.TP
.B :device local
switch back to local configs and unmount the active device
.TP
.B :device
with no arguments, show the currently active device, if any
.TP
.B :theme <name>
switch color theme. built-in themes:
.IR catppuccin ", " dracula ", " gruvbox ", " nord ", " tokyo-night ", " one-dark
.TP
.B :theme
with no arguments, list available themes
.TP
.B :sort <name|date|size>
change sort mode
.TP
.B :reverse
toggle sort order between ascending and descending
.TP
.B :cd
change the root directory used by the file picker
.TP
.B :cd reset
reset the file picker root to ~/.config
.SH FILE PICKER
the built-in file picker replaces ranger. navigate with
.B j/k
or arrow keys,
.B ENTER
to open a directory or select a file,
.B BACKSPACE
to go up a directory, and
.B q
to cancel or quit.
.TP
.B h or help
to show the tutorial again.
.SH ROLLBACK
when
.B rollback
is enabled in settings (default: true), confy automatically saves a compressed backup of a file to
.I /tmp/<filename>.confbak
before opening it for editing. to restore the backup, select the file and run
.B :rb
\&. a confirmation prompt will appear.
.SH REMOTE PROFILES
.B :device <host>
mounts a remote machine's entire filesystem to a local mountpoint under
.I ~/.cache/confy/mounts/
via
.BR sshfs (1)
and switches confy's active view to that host's tracked configs. absolute tracked paths (e.g.
.IR /etc/jail.conf )
are transparently translated to their location under the mount, so stat, preview, edit, and rollback all operate on the real remote file.

while a device is active, the header shows
.I [remote: <host>]
\&. run
.B :device local
to unmount and return to your own configs; the local session's state is preserved exactly as it was.

if the remote host cannot be reached, or is running a version of confy that predates
.IR config.json ,
confy refuses to switch rather than guessing at an incompatible format.
.SH ELEVATED EDITING
.B :su
opens the selected file with root privileges via
.BR pkexec (1)
instead of the normal
.BR $EDITOR " invocation. this operates on whatever local path is currently in view, whether that's a plain local file or a file resolved through an active "
.B :device
mount.

on a mounted device, this matters because sshfs presents remote files under your local user's identity; a remote file owned by a different user (e.g. a root-owned
.IR /etc/pf.conf )
may not be writable through the mount normally. local root, reached via
.BR pkexec ,
can write through the mount regardless, since permissions on the mount are enforced the same way as any other local path.

.B :su
requires
.BR pkexec (1)
(polkit) to be installed. to use
.B :su
while a device is mounted, the local machine additionally needs
.I user_allow_other
uncommented in
.I /etc/fuse.conf
\&, so that a root process can see into a mount owned by an unprivileged user. confy will report clearly if this isn't the case rather than silently opening an empty buffer.
.SH THEMES
confy ships with six built-in themes, set via
.B :theme <name>
in command mode:
.IR catppuccin " (default), " dracula ", " gruvbox ", " nord ", " tokyo-night ", " one-dark
\&. theme changes apply immediately and are saved to
.I config.json
under
.IR settings.theme ", overwriting " settings.colors " with the theme's palette."
.SH PREVIEW PANE
press
.B p
to toggle a live preview pane beside the file list, showing the first lines of the currently selected file. the preview reads through the same path resolution as editing does, so it reflects the real file whether local or on a mounted device. the preference persists across restarts.
.SH CONFIGURATION
confy stores its data and settings in
.I ~/.config/confy/config.json
\&. if an older
.I tracked.json
is found, it will be automatically migrated.

the
.B settings
key in config.json accepts the following options:
.TP
.B rollback
boolean. enable/disable automatic backups before editing. default: true
.TP
.B theme
string. name of the active built-in theme. setting this via
.B :theme
also overwrites
.B colors
with that theme's palette.
.TP
.B colors
object with keys:
.B bg, fg, highlight, group, border
\&. values can be a named color (e.g.
.I "lavender", "cyan", "default"
) or a hex code (e.g.
.I "#cba6f7"
).

example config.json settings block:
.PP
.nf
"settings": {
  "rollback": true,
  "theme": "catppuccin",
  "colors": {
    "bg": "default",
    "fg": "default",
    "highlight": "#cba6f7",
    "group": "#89b4fa"
  }
}
.fi
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/confy/config.json
confy data and settings
.TP
.I /tmp/<filename>.confbak
rollback backups (gzip compressed)
.TP
.I ~/.cache/confy/mounts/<host>/
sshfs mountpoints created by
.B :device
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B EDITOR
the editor used to open config files. defaults to
.B nano
if not set.
